        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "First true words — consistent, intentional use of a sound to refer to a specific object or person — typically appear between 10 and 14 months. 'Mama' and 'dada' used with meaning, 'no,' 'up,' and 'more' are common firsts. Babbling continues alongside and precedes words. No words by 15 months warrants a speech evaluation."
