        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Independent walking typically appears between 9 and 12 months, with the normal range extending to 18 months. Walking at 12 months is average, not a target. Cruising (walking while holding furniture) usually precedes independent walking by 2–3 months. No walking by 18 months warrants evaluation."
