      "name": "How much should a 10-month-old eat?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Breast milk or formula (20–24 oz/day) remains the primary nutrition source through 12 months. Solids are offered 2–3 times per day in soft, finger-food or mashed textures. By 9–12 months, babies typically eat 3–4 tablespoons per meal, 2–3 meals per day, with 1–2 snacks. Appetite varies significantly by day."
      }
